content.p: Print RCWs > Title 82 > Chapter 82.25 > Section 82.25.900 82.25.110 << 82.25.900 >> 82.25.901 PDF RCW 82.25.900 Conflict with federal requirements — 2019 c 445. If any part of this act is found to be in conflict with federal requirements that are a prescribed condition to the allocation of federal funds to the state, the conflicting part of this act is inoperative solely to the extent of the conflict and with respect to the agencies directly affected, and this finding does not affect the operation of the remainder of this act in its application to the agencies concerned. Rules adopted under this act must meet federal requirements that are a necessary condition to the receipt of federal funds by the state. [ 2019 c 445 s 407 .]
